        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Length</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WADDING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4) + bingo potential</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">SHUDDER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Common tiles, bingo</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">MADDEST</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Superlative extension</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">DADDY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Y(4) boosts short word</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">MUDDY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">M(3) + Y(4) + DD</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">ODDLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Double ODD + LY</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">LADDER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Very common word</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">MIDDLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">-DDLE pattern classic</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Short DD Words for Tight Boards</h2>

<p>These compact DD words slot into congested boards while keeping your rack flexible:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ODD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADDED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADDER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BUDDY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CADDY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EDDY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TODDY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span></span>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">DD Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend with -ED and -ING:</span> Many DD words accept common suffixes. ADDED→ADDING, WADDED→WADDING. This turns a 5-letter word into a bingo candidate without needing rare tiles.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use -DDLE as your go-to stem:</span> MIDDLE, RIDDLE, SADDLE, PADDLE, FIDDLE, MUDDLE — the -DDLE pattern produces 6-letter words from extremely common tiles. Memorise these.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ADD is a powerful hook word:</span> ADD hooks onto existing words easily — GADDS, MADDER, ODDS. It also extends backward: L+ADD=LADD, which can become LADDER.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair DD with Y for quick scores:</span> MUDDY(12), DADDY(11), CADDY(12), BUDDY(12), TODDY(10) — the Y tile adds 4 points and these words are short enough to fit anywhere.</p>
  </div>
</div>

